Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer led the U.S. delegation for an international conference on Venezuela in Colombia. During his visit, Finer met with President Gustavo Petro and other Colombian officials to follow up on the recent bilateral meeting between President Biden and President Petro. Finer reiterated the United States' commitment to supporting the Venezuelan people and working with the international community to restore democracy and the rule of law in the country. He outlined a step-by-step approach where concrete actions toward restoring Venezuelan democracy would be met with corresponding sanctions relief by the United States. Finer was accompanied by Special Presidential Advisor for the Americas Chris Dodd, National Security Council Senior Director for Western Hemisphere Affairs Juan Gonzalez, and State Department Deputy Assistant Secretary for Western Hemisphere Affairs Mark Wells.